
brief:      "Halden — a single-origin coffee roastery in Bergen that roasts one lot at a time and names the farm on every bag. A cinematic scroll story about the journey from a hillside in Huila to the cup: the altitude, the hands that pick it, the roast curve, the pour. Mood: premium, calm, cinematic."
reasoning:  claude-sonnet-5   (questions · concept · plan · art-direction)
bulk:       claude-sonnet-5   (section codegen · self-critique; escalates to reasoning on repair)
design:     claude-haiku-4-5-20251001   (legacy/fallback tier)

[1m── PLAN ────────────────────────────────────────────────────[0m
brand:  Halden
mood:   premium, calm
layout: origin-to-proof, editorial-brand-story
sections:
  0. masthead         [36mcinematic[0m/lg  Establish Halden's single premise — one lot at a time, named farm on every bag — as a quiet thesis, not a slogan
  1. the-hillside     [36mimmersive[0m/xl  Ground the story at altitude — the specific farm, elevation, and soil that give this lot its character
  2. the-hands        [36mnarrative[0m/lg  Honor the labor of selective picking — named pickers, ripe-cherry selection, the human cost of single-origin quality
  3. the-crossing     [36meditorial[0m/sm  Mark the transition from farm to Bergen — a quiet beat on distance and care in transit
  4. the-roast-curve  [36masymmetric[0m/lg  Reveal the roaster's craft — reading the bean, the curve, the exact moment of first crack, tuned to this lot alone
  5. the-pour         [36mcinematic[0m/xl  Arrive at the cup — the payoff of the whole journey, rendered as a singular, isolated moment
  6. the-proof        [36meditorial[0m/md  Close on credibility — the named farm on the bag, the lot number, the roast date, making the origin claim verifiable
  7. the-invitation   [36meditorial[0m/sm  Close the story with where to find the roastery in Bergen and how to get this lot before it's gone

